Author: ValerieEmphy
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] Emphy.io - Decentralized lodging ecosystem
Body: Dear community! We are pleased to announce that the second sprint of Emphy beta development is over and we‚Äôd like to share with you some results. During the last sprint, we focused on mobile application development. We already have implemented first screens for user sign in, sign up and onboarding flows. Also, first integration testing of API services was performed. Finally, we added integration with Twilio service that we use for user‚Äôs mobile phone number verification. Our next steps are to deploy mobile application to test environment and start testing the whole flow by ourselves first. Also, we continue working on real estate images processing that users can add to posts.

Author: ValerieEmphy
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] Emphy.io - Decentralized lodging ecosystem
Body: The third sprint of Emphy application development is over and we‚Äôd like to share with you some results! During the last sprint, we focused on the development of both views and backend endpoints for supporting user with uploading advertisements of their property. This functionality includes adding property details, location and images. Currently, it is possible for the landlord to add all details about their property to Emphy system. Furthermore, during this development we made minor improvements to our design in order to provide more user-friendly interface to our customers. Also, there were changes done in customer account management such as support for uploading and verifying documents, account removal and modifying services. Finally, we put on track the testing of mobile version together with API, and in parallel with active development we test a mobile application just before providing it to our beta customers. The next steps of development are related to testing the mobile version together with backend API, implementing the property booking functionality.

Body: Greetings Emphy Community Members!  Emphy team is excited to announce that Emphy Testnet has launched! Recently, we‚Äôve sent out an access to Emphy‚Äôs Beta version to all our community members who have previously registered on our official website for testing the platform on Android. Currently, the following functions are available for testing:  ‚úÖAccount creation/registration function ‚úÖE-mail verification ‚úÖLogin/Logout Functions ‚úÖInventory function that enables to list your property and add detailed description as well as choose a payment method ‚úÖCreating and saving your inventory ‚úÖSearch function ‚úÖView and scroll through the properties  In case you missed an opportunity to register for Emphy‚Äôs Beta testing before, you can still fill out ‚ÄúRequest Early Access‚Äù form on our official website. The variety of additional functions in Emphy ecosystem are still going through different stages of development, from back-end to testing by the development team. Thank you for your support!

Author: ValerieEmphy
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] Emphy.io - Decentralized lodging ecosystem
Body: The Launching Country of Emphy Platform Is Kenya!  Emphy Team is thrilled to announce that the launching country of Emphy Platform is Kenya! We consider Emphy as a great solution for Kenyan travel industry, as the country has high percentage of unbanked population, yet has huge interest from tourist side. Furthermore, statistics show that the market is continually growing (143% growth in in 2017), for instance the number of guests in vacation rental properties was 39,500 in the past year. We also look at impressive numbers of smartphone penetration in Kenya that became a global leader in share of internet traffic coming from mobile (83% in 2017), which means that our mobile application will unlock the full potential of the Emphy ecosystem for first adopters in Kenya.  Our team also considers the fact that events in the industry may rapidly change, therefore, in case the government of Kenya bans or puts cryptocurrencies under threat, we would be compelled to change the launching country.

Author: fishervwb
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] Emphy.io - Decentralized lodging ecosystem
Body: How Blockchain and Smart Contracts will Make Difference in Developing Countries  The public sector is a complex mechanism and centralized system that is developed differently in every country. Therefore, the effectiveness of public administrations as such, as well as coverage of the needs of population depends on how well the public system is developed. Sometimes, the complexities in the interaction of a person and the system cause the rapid growth of intermediaries. The more intermediaries‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääthe more expensive and more complicated the service becomes. In the countries where public sector organized properly and has trust of its citizens, there are fewer opportunities to disclose the potential of blockchain. Nevertheless, in those areas where the level of such trust is low, and public institutions are struck by corruption, blockchain becomes an effective alternative. For instance, countries such as Latin America, Central and South Africa and South Asia are far behind the leaders in this area. Except this, the areas with volatile currency, high inflation and political problems will definitely benefit from blockchain transfers.  In fact, international money transfers are vital for millions of people in developing countries, who receive transactions from countries with developed economic system. However, a quick and inexpensive way to transfer money from‚Ä¶ let‚Äôs say, Europe to South Asia, does not really exist. Most people are accustomed to using swift payments or international money transfer systems, such as Western Union, however, this requires considerable time and expensive commissions. Consequently, blockchain technology allows to achieve almost instant payments without any intermediaries: most transactions can be executed within 1 minute regardless of the distance between the participants of the transaction. Moreover, each transaction is recorded in the public register, which contributes to transparency and a decrease in mistrust between counterparts.  To continue, blockchain also offers unprecedented transparency together with the smart contract functionality that makes it possible to set certain rules: for instance, if a payment is received, a document about the transfer of ownership is produced automatically. Furthermore, any attempts to modify previously recorded information will be visible to everyone in the network, so the efforts of any changes will be identified immediately.  Generally speaking, these are one of the biggest opportunities blockchain can bring in the evolution of less developed areas. Emphy believes that in the near future blockchain technology will cover even more spheres of human activity, making the life easier for many people all around the world. Our team works hard to further develop Emphy lodgining ecosystem, where landlords and tenants meet to conclude short-term real estate rental contracts. Blockchain combined with smart contracts will eliminate the dependence on the centralized system between the participants of the transaction, and will significantly reduce the commission and help fixing the terms of the agreement (booking and general conditions) between the owner of the property and the guest. Emphy provides innovative approaches, openness, convenience and ease of use. The platform will raise the technology and the process of short-term renting to a new level of development. Additionally, our team is interested not only in creating a popular decentralized ecosystem for short-term lodging, but also for the EmphyCoin owners to receive direct economic benefits both at an early stage of contribution and in the future. The limited release of tokens and stable demand for them due to the growing number of concluded rent smart contracts will increase their market value, and the real possibilities of using them will help to stabilize the volatility of the crypto currency rate.  https://medium.com/@EmphyOfficial/how-blockchain-and-smart-contracts-will-make-difference-in-developing-countries-7820b4d27753

Author: EmphyOfficial
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] Emphy.io - Decentralized lodging ecosystem
Body: That is correct. Ambisafe is the provider of our smart contract. We are very proud to cooperate with such market leader, because it gives confidence in contract security and reliability. As for stock exchanges we have sent token submission requests to such stocks as: EtherDelta, Yobit, Livecoin, Mercatox, Tidex, Idex, Changelly, Liqui and many others. So far we got several feedbacks, saying that we meet their requirements. We are waiting for more or less full feedback list, so we can get full overview and decide which ones are the best for us.

To make the project even more attractive to existing as well as potential contributors we have decided to revisit our soft and hard caps. We have reviewed and maximally optimized all costs associated with the development and launch of the #Emphy ecosystem.  As a result, we came up with following changes: ‚û°Reduce Emphy Hard cap from 7,260,000 USD to 1,000,000 USD ‚û°Reduce Emphy Soft cap from 1,000,000 USD to 350,000 USD ‚û°Reduce the release of Emphy tokens from 100,000,000 EPY to 15,375,000 EPY Considering these changes our SOFT CAP is 138,2% FUNDED and HARD CAP is 48,3% FUNDED.  Below you can see a comparison of new and old token distribution structures as well as a comparison between the crowdfunding structure.         All contributors, who have already participated in Emphy ICO purchased our tokens for $0.08. ‚ùóAll unsold tokens after the end of the ICO will be sent to the Emphy Marketing Fund. 1. All unsold tokens after the end of the ICO will be directed to a special wallet and will form a separate part of the marketing structure. This new structure is the Emphy Marketing Fund. 2. Tokens sent to the marketing fund will be frozen until March 15, 2018. 3. Since March 16th, 2018, the Emphy team, if necessary, can sell on the exchange every month up to 600,000 EPY from the marketing fund. 4. The sale price of the #EPY token from the marketing fund on the exchange cannot be less than $0.15. 5. The wallet addresses of marketing fund will be published on Facebook, Twitter and Telegram. Each contributor can verify that the Emphy team fulfills its obligations. Big thanks for all who are supporting us!

Author: EmphyOfficial
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] Emphy.io - Decentralized lodging ecosystem
Body: It is definitely not a hotel project. At the same time we don't position ourselves as just a decentralized copy of Airbnb.  Our product is a mobile app that you can use for either finding interesting and affordable renting ads for travelling, or, if you want to rent your property to some travelers, create ad in few easy steps.  Decentralized nature of the app will bring new users to the ecosystem, especially those who don't want or have no ability to use their bank account. At the same time we are adding useful features, like virtual tours, that provide 360 degree view of the room (which can also be created by a landlord with his smartphone). We also adding user bonuses for leaving ratings and some other actions to both landlords and travellers. Think of it as of a nice cashback after you leave home. We believe that this should enhance overall security, so both sides of the deal could feel themselves much more secured. There are many more features, please visit our site to see them.
